The paper deals with the problem of disentangling 3D face shape representation, which involves computer vision (CV) and graphics (GR) techniques. The proposed method involves encoding and decoding in a nonlinear way, which is related to machine learning (LG) and multimedia (MM) fields. The paper also mentions the use of attribute decomposition framework, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (AI) research. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.MM, and cs.AI.
